\date{2026-05-20T12:19:20Z}
\author{eigil-rischel}
\import{macros}
\title{Markov Promonad}
\taxon{Definition}
\p{
  Let #{\cC} be a Markov category. Recall that a \em{promonad} may be defined as an identity-on-objects functor #{\cC \to \cC_s}. If #{\cC_s} admits a symmetric monoidal structure which makes this a \em{strict} monoidal functor, and which is furthermore semicartesian, observe that the copy maps in #{\cC} push forward to copy maps in #{\cC_s}, so that #{\cC_s} acquires a unique Markov structure where this is a Markov functor. In this case we call this promonad a \em{Markov promonad}.
}